BEIJING, June 23 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Government has banned the picking and trade of wild algae and excessive digging of licorice and Chinese ephedra in northern China in a bid to protect the fragile ecological environment.
   NEW YORK _ When the latest book on herbal remedies landed on my desk, my first reaction was to put it in the giveaway pile with all the rest of the home remedy books, especially after Page 1 brought me face to face with cures like gin-soaked raisins for arthritis and Archway coconut macaroons for diarrhea.
